cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper deals with out-of-distribution detection using deep generative models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and graphics (cs.GR). The paper specifically focuses on a generative model known as neural rendering model (NRM), which is a type of deep generative model used for image synthesis and manipulation, and hence, it is more likely to be classified under cs.CV and cs.GR. However, since the paper deals with machine learning and neural networks, it could also be classified under cs.LG and cs.NE. Finally, since the paper deals with the detection of out-of-distribution data, it could also be classified under cs.AI.
